1
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:55,000
"Lost To You"

2
00:00:55,100 --> 00:00:57,700
(Episode 2)

3
00:00:58,750 --> 00:00:59,750
The rain will stop.

4
00:01:00,708 --> 00:01:02,208
But some marks, once they're made,

5
00:01:03,583 --> 00:01:04,666
can never be erased.

6
00:01:10,541 --> 00:01:11,291
Oh my god.

7
00:01:11,292 --> 00:01:12,791
He's first in our grade again.

8
00:01:13,500 --> 00:01:14,666
How many times is that now?

9
00:01:15,541 --> 00:01:16,541
Top student.

10
00:01:16,750 --> 00:01:17,750
So handsome.

11
00:01:18,041 --> 00:01:19,041
Single-parent family.

12
00:01:20,375 --> 00:01:21,833
The tragic hero.

13
00:01:22,333 --> 00:01:23,166
We're not on the list again.

14
00:01:23,291 --> 00:01:24,291
Let's go, let's go.

15
00:01:24,791 --> 00:01:25,791
Zhan Wang. Zhan Wang.

16
00:01:25,833 --> 00:01:27,767
Yesterday, he said he'd
be friends with Xu Yuan.

17
00:01:27,791 --> 00:01:29,375
And now he dares to sit with the Jinx.

18
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,375
Good grades, huh?

19
00:01:36,625 --> 00:01:37,625
That's hilarious.

20
00:01:37,833 --> 00:01:38,833
Hilarious, right?

21
00:01:38,916 --> 00:01:40,458
What a waste of a handsome face.

22
00:01:41,583 --> 00:01:42,791
The power of that Jinx...

23
00:01:42,875 --> 00:01:43,875
is no joke.

24
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:44,583
Just you wait.

25
00:01:44,666 --> 00:01:46,026
He's in for some serious bad luck.

26
00:02:09,333 --> 00:02:10,333
Let's make a deal.

27
00:02:10,666 --> 00:02:11,946
Give me back my grandma's house.

28
00:02:12,666 --> 00:02:14,541
I'll pay market price plus twenty percent.

29
00:02:15,416 --> 00:02:16,416
I'll take the loss.

30
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:18,000
Impossible.

31
00:02:19,791 --> 00:02:21,291
You're putting on quite an act.

32
00:02:22,583 --> 00:02:23,666
Don't you need money?

33
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Another twenty percent.

34
00:02:26,583 --> 00:02:27,583
How about it?

35
00:02:30,625 --> 00:02:32,041
Granny Chang left the house to me.

36
00:02:32,875 --> 00:02:34,355
If I need money, I'll earn it myself.

37
00:02:35,208 --> 00:02:36,208
Earn it yourself?

38
00:02:38,791 --> 00:02:39,791
By doing...

39
00:02:40,541 --> 00:02:41,541
manual labor?

40
00:02:48,250 --> 00:02:49,250
How about this?

41
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:51,500
I'll hire you.

42
00:02:52,375 --> 00:02:53,375
To tutor me.

43
00:02:54,166 --> 00:02:55,166
Tutor you in what?

44
00:02:56,208 --> 00:02:57,208
Boxing.

45
00:02:57,416 --> 00:02:58,416
Boxing?

46
00:02:59,375 --> 00:02:59,916
I don't know how.

47
00:03:00,250 --> 00:03:00,791
Find someone else.

48
00:03:01,250 --> 00:03:02,375
Aren't you the top student?

49
00:03:05,708 --> 00:03:07,166
I'll hire you for two hours a day.

50
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:08,916
Five hundred an hour.

51
00:03:09,493 --> 00:03:11,409
That's a thousand a day.

52
00:03:11,916 --> 00:03:13,375
Ten thousand in ten days.

53
00:03:14,166 --> 00:03:14,875
Twenty days...

54
00:03:15,041 --> 00:03:16,125
You do the math.

55
00:03:16,150 --> 00:03:17,630
[TN: This is all incredibly Fake
looking money. Bank of Huag???]

56
00:03:23,041 --> 00:03:24,041
Why me?

57
00:03:24,583 --> 00:03:25,583
I just want to see...

58
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:28,573
what you're willing to do...

59
00:03:29,416 --> 00:03:30,416
for money.

60
00:03:35,166 --> 00:03:35,875
Just as a sparring partner?

61
00:03:36,083 --> 00:03:37,083
Of course not.

62
00:03:39,416 --> 00:03:41,041
You'll serve me tea and water,

63
00:03:41,250 --> 00:03:42,375
run errands,

64
00:03:42,708 --> 00:03:43,767
and be at my beck and call.

65
00:03:43,791 --> 00:03:44,791
To put it bluntly,

66
00:03:45,041 --> 00:03:46,041
you'll be my gofer.

67
00:03:47,875 --> 00:03:48,915
You need money, don't you?

68
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:50,750
You can steal a house,

69
00:03:51,583 --> 00:03:52,583
you can haul bricks.

70
00:03:53,375 --> 00:03:55,083
What's being a gofer compared to that?

71
00:04:04,791 --> 00:04:05,791
Deal.

72
00:04:07,583 --> 00:04:08,583
When do we start?

73
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:10,416
Today.

74
00:04:10,791 --> 00:04:12,031
Go to my house and wait for me.

75
00:05:07,208 --> 00:05:08,208
Come in.

76
00:05:09,166 --> 00:05:10,166
Leave your shoes outside.

77
00:05:10,375 --> 00:05:11,458
Don't get my house dirty.

78
00:05:25,083 --> 00:05:26,726
Do you know how long
I made you stand there?

79
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:27,750
Ten minutes.

80
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Feeling wronged?

81
00:05:30,375 --> 00:05:31,375
It's your money, anyway.

82
00:05:31,916 --> 00:05:32,916
Five hundred an hour.

83
00:05:33,583 --> 00:05:35,063
What do I have to feel wronged about?

84
00:05:35,166 --> 00:05:36,166
Alright.

85
00:05:37,333 --> 00:05:38,333
Have a seat.

86
00:05:43,458 --> 00:05:44,858
Let's get the rules straight first.

87
00:05:45,125 --> 00:05:45,666
First.

88
00:05:45,958 --> 00:05:46,958
When you're here,

89
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:49,113
you have to call me Master Zhan.

90
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:52,833
What?

91
00:05:53,458 --> 00:05:54,458
Cat got your tongue?

92
00:05:55,916 --> 00:05:56,916
Master Zhan.

93
00:05:58,500 --> 00:05:59,500
Second.

94
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:03,020
When I ask you a question, you answer.

95
00:06:03,250 --> 00:06:04,250
You must use 'Yes'

96
00:06:04,416 --> 00:06:05,416
or 'Understood.'

97
00:06:05,583 --> 00:06:06,903
And add 'Master Zhan' at the end.

98
00:06:07,458 --> 00:06:08,458
Is that clear?

99
00:06:08,958 --> 00:06:09,958
Understood.

100
00:06:10,125 --> 00:06:11,125
Master Zhan.

101
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:19,500
What are you smiling at?

102
00:06:20,125 --> 00:06:21,125
I'm not smiling.

103
00:06:21,541 --> 00:06:22,541
Master.

104
00:06:24,250 --> 00:06:25,250
Third.

105
00:06:25,333 --> 00:06:26,458
Go get me a cup of coffee.

106
00:06:27,125 --> 00:06:28,625
No sugar, no milk.

107
00:06:29,083 --> 00:06:30,483
The temperature must be 75 degrees.

108
00:06:30,583 --> 00:06:32,063
There's a thermometer in the kitchen.

109
00:06:33,666 --> 00:06:34,666
Fine.

110
00:07:01,125 --> 00:07:02,125
Too bitter.

111
00:07:03,291 --> 00:07:04,291
Wipe it up.

112
00:07:23,166 --> 00:07:24,166
In her last year,

113
00:07:24,458 --> 00:07:25,818
is this how you served my grandma?

114
00:07:27,125 --> 00:07:28,125
No.

115
00:07:29,833 --> 00:07:31,753
Granny Chang never
made things difficult for me.

116
00:07:43,458 --> 00:07:44,458
Time to practice.

117
00:07:47,291 --> 00:07:47,708
Catch.

118
00:07:48,166 --> 00:07:49,166
Put them on.

119
00:07:49,958 --> 00:07:50,958
The rules are simple.

120
00:07:51,333 --> 00:07:52,833
I punch, you block.

121
00:07:53,375 --> 00:07:54,125
No dodging.

122
00:07:54,291 --> 00:07:55,291
You have to take the hit.

123
00:07:55,458 --> 00:07:56,458
Understood.

124
00:07:56,583 --> 00:07:57,583
Understood.

125
00:07:59,791 --> 00:08:01,083
Add 'Master Zhan' at the end.

126
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:03,791
Understood, Master Zhan.

127
00:08:05,666 --> 00:08:06,666
Put them on properly.

128
00:08:06,750 --> 00:08:08,310
Don't blame me if you get a concussion.

129
00:08:11,125 --> 00:08:12,525
Where's my family's osmanthus tree?

130
00:08:13,458 --> 00:08:14,898
A typhoon knocked it down last year.

131
00:08:15,208 --> 00:08:16,848
What about the grape trellis in the yard?

132
00:08:16,916 --> 00:08:17,916
It was taken down.

133
00:08:18,041 --> 00:08:19,226
My mom said it attracted snakes.

134
00:08:19,250 --> 00:08:20,083
What about the orange cat?

135
00:08:20,208 --> 00:08:21,768
Three months after Grandma passed away,

136
00:08:21,916 --> 00:08:22,583
it died.

137
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:23,870
You seem to know everything.

138
00:08:24,333 --> 00:08:25,733
I lived here for seven whole years.

139
00:08:26,375 --> 00:08:27,735
And you were gone for seven years.

140
00:08:27,833 --> 00:08:28,833
Shut up.

141
00:08:30,541 --> 00:08:31,541
What do you know?

142
00:08:33,041 --> 00:08:34,041
Get up.

143
00:08:34,375 --> 00:08:35,375
Let's continue.

144
00:09:40,125 --> 00:09:41,125
Here's today's pay.

145
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:44,500
What time tomorrow?

146
00:09:45,416 --> 00:09:46,416
Depends on my mood.

147
00:09:49,833 --> 00:09:50,833
Alright.

148
00:10:12,458 --> 00:10:13,458
Jinx.

149
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:17,333
Carry my bag for a bit.

150
00:10:18,375 --> 00:10:19,375
I'll pay you.

151
00:10:19,625 --> 00:10:20,625
Manual labor counts too.

152
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:43,416
Why are you so tired?

153
00:11:00,208 --> 00:11:01,291
Hurry up.

154
00:11:09,708 --> 00:11:11,548
The Jinx is carrying his
bag? What's going on?

155
00:11:19,659 --> 00:11:20,659
A brick.

156
00:11:23,291 --> 00:11:24,291
Three of them!

157
00:11:25,541 --> 00:11:26,541
Jinx.

158
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,000
Finish all of this.

159
00:11:31,708 --> 00:11:32,208
Why?

160
00:11:32,708 --> 00:11:33,791
I'm paying you.

161
00:11:34,208 --> 00:11:36,088
You should throw in
some extra services, right?

162
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:39,708
Which chapter?

163
00:11:40,041 --> 00:11:41,041
All of it.

164
00:11:45,791 --> 00:11:46,875
The entire workbook.

165
00:11:58,958 --> 00:11:59,958
Let's go eat.

166
00:12:00,250 --> 00:12:00,791
What do you want to eat?

167
00:12:00,791 --> 00:12:01,041
Let's go.

168
00:12:01,041 --> 00:12:02,041
I want fish balls.

169
00:12:02,125 --> 00:12:02,541
Let's go.

170
00:12:02,916 --> 00:12:03,996
Come on, let's go together.

171
00:12:05,083 --> 00:12:06,083
Let's go.

172
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:11,500
Aren't you going to eat?

173
00:12:24,708 --> 00:12:25,708
Stop writing.

174
00:12:28,791 --> 00:12:30,711
If you're being bullied,
you have to fight back.

175
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:32,713
Cowering like that...
What kind of man are you?

176
00:12:37,708 --> 00:12:38,375
What are you doing?

177
00:12:38,458 --> 00:12:39,458
Bian Ye.

178
00:12:40,375 --> 00:12:40,791
Fuck!

179
00:12:40,916 --> 00:12:41,500
Who are you?

180
00:12:41,666 --> 00:12:43,226
Bullying a classmate in broad daylight.

181
00:12:43,333 --> 00:12:44,453
This is what you get.

182
00:12:47,666 --> 00:12:48,750
Who the hell are you?

183
00:12:49,375 --> 00:12:49,916
Take this!

184
00:12:49,916 --> 00:12:50,250
Zhan Wang!

185
00:12:50,250 --> 00:12:50,708
Are you crazy?

186
00:12:50,708 --> 00:12:51,625
It's not him! Stop fighting!

187
00:12:51,625 --> 00:12:52,625
It's not him!

188
00:12:53,416 --> 00:12:53,750
Stop fighting!

189
00:12:53,750 --> 00:12:54,750
What are you all doing?

190
00:12:55,125 --> 00:12:56,166
Zhan Wang, stop fighting!

191
00:12:56,708 --> 00:12:57,708
Bian Ye! Zhan Wang!

192
00:12:58,166 --> 00:12:59,166
Come out.

193
00:13:02,750 --> 00:13:03,750
Teacher.

194
00:13:03,826 --> 00:13:06,616
This redhead was bullying a student.

195
00:13:08,666 --> 00:13:09,166
Teacher.

196
00:13:09,458 --> 00:13:10,458
He didn't bring lunch.

197
00:13:10,750 --> 00:13:12,059
His mom asked me to bring him some food.

198
00:13:12,083 --> 00:13:13,883
This guy just came up
and started hitting me.

199
00:13:14,291 --> 00:13:15,583
What exactly happened?

200
00:13:15,909 --> 00:13:16,909
Xu Yuan, speak.

201
00:13:17,416 --> 00:13:18,416
Teacher.

202
00:13:18,833 --> 00:13:20,393
My mom asked Bian Ye to bring me lunch.

203
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,000
Zhan Wang misunderstood.

204
00:13:22,833 --> 00:13:23,958
Bian Ye wasn't bullying me.

205
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,000
That black stuff...

206
00:13:27,458 --> 00:13:28,458
is rice?

207
00:13:31,916 --> 00:13:32,750
What are you looking at?

208
00:13:32,875 --> 00:13:33,934
I'm looking at you. Got a problem?

209
00:13:33,958 --> 00:13:34,750
Are you stupid?

210
00:13:34,751 --> 00:13:35,851
Got a problem? Let's go after school.

211
00:13:35,875 --> 00:13:36,875
Bring it on. Let's go.

212
00:13:36,916 --> 00:13:38,226
- See you at the warehouse dock after school.
- Still fighting?

213
00:13:38,250 --> 00:13:39,666
Are you still going to argue?

214
00:13:39,833 --> 00:13:41,333
It's only the second day of school.

215
00:13:41,666 --> 00:13:42,916
Fighting on the second day.

216
00:13:43,625 --> 00:13:44,666
Bian Ye.

217
00:13:44,833 --> 00:13:45,500
You're a senior now.

218
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:46,458
You've already been
held back for two years.

219
00:13:46,458 --> 00:13:47,166
You skip class every day.

220
00:13:47,250 --> 00:13:48,392
And when you do show up, you cause trouble.

221
00:13:48,416 --> 00:13:49,892
If you keep hanging out with those thugs...

222
00:13:49,916 --> 00:13:50,916
you're finished.

223
00:13:51,208 --> 00:13:52,208
Teacher.

224
00:13:52,333 --> 00:13:53,333
My family needs money.

225
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:55,101
How else am I supposed to get by?

226
00:13:55,125 --> 00:13:56,351
Are you going to give it to me?

227
00:13:56,375 --> 00:13:56,958
Also, Teacher...

228
00:13:57,375 --> 00:13:58,208
We were both fighting.

229
00:13:58,375 --> 00:13:59,500
Don't play favorites.

230
00:13:59,618 --> 00:14:00,618
He threw the first punch.

231
00:14:01,416 --> 00:14:03,434
Is it because he's some
young master from Jingzhou?

232
00:14:03,458 --> 00:14:04,666
Are you okay?

233
00:14:04,791 --> 00:14:05,791
What's the matter?

234
00:14:07,458 --> 00:14:08,458
Zhan Wang.

235
00:14:09,250 --> 00:14:09,666
Teacher.

236
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:10,500
I don't think he's feeling well.

237
00:14:10,666 --> 00:14:11,809
I'll take him to the nurse's office.

238
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:12,833
Okay.

239
00:14:13,875 --> 00:14:14,875
Wimp.

240
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:23,333
You're awake.

241
00:14:24,541 --> 00:14:25,541
Two.

242
00:14:27,666 --> 00:14:29,375
How could I have such a disgusting son?

243
00:14:29,583 --> 00:14:30,809
Do you know what you did wrong?

244
00:14:30,833 --> 00:14:31,833
I did nothing wrong.

245
00:14:37,083 --> 00:14:38,083
I did nothing wrong.

246
00:14:43,083 --> 00:14:44,083
How are you feeling?

247
00:14:44,166 --> 00:14:45,166
What are you doing here?

248
00:14:45,291 --> 00:14:46,731
I came back to Hongzhen a while ago.

249
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,000
Now...

250
00:14:48,208 --> 00:14:50,008
I'm working part-time
as the school nurse.

251
00:14:50,958 --> 00:14:51,416
Don't move.

252
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:52,750
How are you feeling?

253
00:14:53,458 --> 00:14:54,458
Dizzy.

254
00:14:54,916 --> 00:14:55,916
Nauseous.

255
00:14:56,416 --> 00:14:57,416
Blurry vision.

256
00:14:57,500 --> 00:14:58,500
I'm fine.

257
00:14:58,625 --> 00:14:59,665
It's just low blood sugar.

258
00:14:59,750 --> 00:15:01,476
Low blood sugar wouldn't
cause this kind of...

259
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:03,300
sudden, temporary
loss of consciousness...

260
00:15:03,458 --> 00:15:04,658
accompanied by stiff limbs.

261
00:15:05,291 --> 00:15:05,750
Xiao Wang.

262
00:15:06,250 --> 00:15:07,410
What's really wrong with you?

263
00:15:08,208 --> 00:15:09,208
Tell your brother.

264
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:10,500
Brother.

265
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:13,041
You're not my brother.

266
00:15:13,625 --> 00:15:15,065
The Zhan family has no one like you.

267
00:15:16,458 --> 00:15:17,458
I have to get to class.

268
00:15:19,125 --> 00:15:20,291
I'm the school nurse here.

269
00:15:20,791 --> 00:15:22,583
You can't leave in your condition.

270
00:15:23,250 --> 00:15:24,250
Besides...

271
00:15:25,125 --> 00:15:26,208
I'm also your guardian.

272
00:15:26,333 --> 00:15:27,333
Guardian?

273
00:15:28,083 --> 00:15:29,726
Someone who was kicked out of the house...

274
00:15:29,750 --> 00:15:30,950
and disowned by the family?

275
00:15:37,625 --> 00:15:38,705
Even if I was kicked out...

276
00:15:39,625 --> 00:15:40,665
I'm still your brother.

277
00:15:42,416 --> 00:15:43,416
Zhan Wang.

278
00:15:43,583 --> 00:15:44,583
Are you okay?

279
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,000
I'm fine now.

280
00:15:47,291 --> 00:15:47,750
Xu Yuan.

281
00:15:48,166 --> 00:15:48,666
Get me out of here.

282
00:15:49,041 --> 00:15:49,583
Xiao Wang.

283
00:15:49,666 --> 00:15:50,666
Hurry.

284
00:16:07,291 --> 00:16:08,291
I'm sorry.

285
00:16:08,375 --> 00:16:08,916
It's all my fault.

286
00:16:09,208 --> 00:16:10,333
When you're around me...

287
00:16:10,791 --> 00:16:11,991
It has nothing to do with you.

288
00:16:12,458 --> 00:16:13,458
It was me.

289
00:16:17,125 --> 00:16:19,291
I just couldn't stand that redhead.

290
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,000
That workbook...

291
00:16:25,041 --> 00:16:26,041
give it back to me.

292
00:16:26,125 --> 00:16:27,405
You don't have to do it anymore.

293
00:16:33,875 --> 00:16:34,875
I get it.

294
00:16:35,416 --> 00:16:36,736
I'll give it back this afternoon.

295
00:16:40,291 --> 00:16:41,666
That's not what I meant.

296
00:16:46,666 --> 00:16:47,541
He's so handsome.

297
00:16:47,625 --> 00:16:48,625
So handsome.

298
00:16:49,666 --> 00:16:50,666
So handsome.

299
00:16:57,291 --> 00:16:58,541
Even his warm-ups are handsome.

300
00:17:01,125 --> 00:17:02,125
Xu Yuan.

301
00:17:03,250 --> 00:17:05,041
Is it because you don't exercise...

302
00:17:05,583 --> 00:17:07,783
that you're this out of
breath from carrying my bag?

303
00:17:08,583 --> 00:17:10,750
I go for a run by the sea every night.

304
00:17:12,416 --> 00:17:14,000
Exercising alone is so boring.

305
00:17:15,291 --> 00:17:16,531
You need to be part of a group.

306
00:17:22,333 --> 00:17:24,053
How about this? I'll take you to play ball.

307
00:17:25,083 --> 00:17:26,083
Zhan Wang.

308
00:17:27,416 --> 00:17:28,536
Can you stop messing around?

309
00:17:28,708 --> 00:17:30,428
All these girls are here to watch you play.

310
00:17:30,458 --> 00:17:31,458
If you bring him along...

311
00:17:32,250 --> 00:17:34,208
who would want to
see the guy they like...

312
00:17:34,375 --> 00:17:35,583
get hurt because of him?

313
00:17:35,875 --> 00:17:36,875
Yeah.

314
00:17:37,166 --> 00:17:37,750
You guys go ahead and play.

315
00:17:38,166 --> 00:17:39,166
I'm not very good at it.

316
00:17:41,291 --> 00:17:42,291
Stop, Zhan Wang.

317
00:17:44,458 --> 00:17:45,458
Stop.

318
00:17:48,750 --> 00:17:49,750
Zhan Wang.

319
00:17:50,208 --> 00:17:50,958
I've had enough.

320
00:17:51,125 --> 00:17:52,125
I've really had enough.

321
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:53,250
I don't care if you...

322
00:17:53,291 --> 00:17:54,731
genuinely want to be my friend...

323
00:17:55,125 --> 00:17:56,851
or if you just think
it's fun to mess with me.

324
00:17:56,875 --> 00:17:57,875
Let's just end it here.

325
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,000
Stay away from me.

326
00:18:00,583 --> 00:18:01,583
It's better for everyone.

327
00:18:01,958 --> 00:18:03,125
That's not what I meant.

328
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:06,500
Watch out!

329
00:18:11,458 --> 00:18:12,458
See?

330
00:18:13,125 --> 00:18:14,125
It happened again.

331
00:18:14,875 --> 00:18:15,875
I always...

332
00:18:16,375 --> 00:18:18,175
end up dragging down
the people around me.

333
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:28,500
Xu Yuan.

334
00:18:29,166 --> 00:18:30,291
Don't you dare say that.

335
00:18:30,750 --> 00:18:33,030
I, Zhan Wang, don't believe
in any of that jinx nonsense.

336
00:18:33,375 --> 00:18:34,695
You're the one who just saved me.

337
00:18:41,750 --> 00:18:42,750
Your hand is hurt.

338
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:44,583
Let's go to the nurse's office.

339
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,708
It's fine. I'll take care of it at home.

340
00:18:48,291 --> 00:18:49,291
Let's go.

341
00:18:54,583 --> 00:18:55,583
Student Zhan Wang.

342
00:18:56,208 --> 00:18:56,833
We meet again.

343
00:18:57,166 --> 00:18:58,166
At this rate...

344
00:18:59,541 --> 00:19:00,041
What is it?

345
00:19:00,416 --> 00:19:01,500
Was it a fight this time?

346
00:19:02,041 --> 00:19:03,041
Or...

347
00:19:04,250 --> 00:19:05,250
an accident?

348
00:19:05,750 --> 00:19:06,750
He scraped his hand.

349
00:19:06,875 --> 00:19:07,875
Take care of it.

350
00:19:08,166 --> 00:19:09,291
Here, let me see.

351
00:19:24,916 --> 00:19:25,916
It's a scrape.

352
00:19:26,041 --> 00:19:27,041
Bleeding a little.

353
00:19:27,208 --> 00:19:28,968
It just needs to be
cleaned and disinfected.

354
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,583
You two are inseparable, aren't you?

355
00:19:33,958 --> 00:19:34,958
Mind your own business.

356
00:19:35,291 --> 00:19:36,291
I have to take a call.

357
00:19:37,625 --> 00:19:38,625
You.

358
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:41,583
Just clean it for him.

359
00:19:42,416 --> 00:19:43,896
The iodine and cotton swabs are here.

360
00:19:45,208 --> 00:19:46,208
Me?

361
00:19:47,458 --> 00:19:48,458
Your mess.

362
00:19:48,875 --> 00:19:49,875
You clean it up.

363
00:19:51,250 --> 00:19:52,250
It's fine.

364
00:19:52,375 --> 00:19:53,916
Xu Yuan can tell you what to do.

365
00:19:55,416 --> 00:19:56,656
He's practically my apprentice.

366
00:20:05,958 --> 00:20:07,038
He's doing this on purpose.

367
00:20:07,416 --> 00:20:08,750
Dr. Zhan.

368
00:20:12,708 --> 00:20:13,708
You two know each other?

369
00:20:13,875 --> 00:20:14,875
Sort of.

370
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:16,333
He's my older brother.

371
00:20:17,375 --> 00:20:18,375
Sort of?

372
00:20:24,416 --> 00:20:25,416
Tell me if it hurts.

373
00:21:05,041 --> 00:21:06,041
Idiot.

374
00:21:06,958 --> 00:21:08,398
Did you have to jump in front of me?

375
00:21:10,041 --> 00:21:11,333
And you got yourself hurt.

376
00:21:15,541 --> 00:21:16,661
Your head is more important.

377
00:21:18,041 --> 00:21:19,041
My head...

378
00:21:19,416 --> 00:21:20,416
what's it to you?

379
00:21:22,291 --> 00:21:23,291
Because...

380
00:21:24,625 --> 00:21:25,500
I'm a jinx.

381
00:21:25,625 --> 00:21:26,625
Nonsense.

382
00:21:27,083 --> 00:21:28,333
I don't believe that.

383
00:21:31,583 --> 00:21:32,583
Xu Yuan.

384
00:21:32,625 --> 00:21:34,083
You say you're a jinx...

385
00:21:34,250 --> 00:21:35,970
but does that jinx work on yourself too?

386
00:21:36,375 --> 00:21:37,775
Why is it that after I showed up...

387
00:21:38,250 --> 00:21:39,650
you started having bad luck too?

388
00:21:45,375 --> 00:21:46,958
I wish it were only me.

389
00:21:56,166 --> 00:21:57,166
Is it wrapped up?

390
00:21:59,958 --> 00:22:01,166
If it is, let's go to class.

391
00:22:17,208 --> 00:22:18,267
Let's go see a movie later.

392
00:22:18,291 --> 00:22:18,666
Let's go.

393
00:22:18,666 --> 00:22:19,666
Yeah, sure. Let's go.

394
00:22:19,833 --> 00:22:20,125
Let me tell you...

395
00:22:20,126 --> 00:22:21,208
that movie is awesome.

396
00:22:21,375 --> 00:22:22,375
That kid, Zhan Wang...

397
00:22:22,875 --> 00:22:23,875
chickened out.

398
00:22:29,416 --> 00:22:30,416
Waiting for Zhan Wang?

399
00:22:33,041 --> 00:22:34,041
None of your business.

400
00:22:34,125 --> 00:22:36,045
Does the school nurse
manage student fights now?

401
00:22:36,666 --> 00:22:37,666
Just a suggestion.

402
00:22:38,458 --> 00:22:39,458
I suggest...

403
00:22:39,916 --> 00:22:40,708
you stop bothering him.

404
00:22:40,875 --> 00:22:41,875
Says who?

405
00:22:42,125 --> 00:22:44,005
What gives you the
right to tell me what to do?

406
00:22:54,541 --> 00:22:55,981
That kid's not here again. Let's go.

407
00:23:00,875 --> 00:23:01,875
You know him?

408
00:23:04,500 --> 00:23:05,500
You're so nosy.

409
00:23:22,208 --> 00:23:22,791
Not bad.

410
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:23,666
Right on time.

411
00:23:23,833 --> 00:23:25,708
Let's make this quick.
Saves us the trouble.

412
00:23:25,875 --> 00:23:26,875
Bian Ye.

413
00:23:28,166 --> 00:23:29,291
Finally found you.

414
00:23:30,041 --> 00:23:31,121
The score from last time...

415
00:23:31,666 --> 00:23:32,706
it's time to settle it.

416
00:23:32,916 --> 00:23:33,916
Brother Hua.

417
00:23:34,250 --> 00:23:35,730
I swear I'll pay you back next month.

418
00:23:36,208 --> 00:23:37,208
Next month?

419
00:23:37,416 --> 00:23:38,416
I want it now.

420
00:23:41,666 --> 00:23:42,726
This has nothing to do with you.

421
00:23:42,750 --> 00:23:43,750
You should go.

422
00:23:43,958 --> 00:23:45,333
We'll deal with our stuff later.

423
00:23:45,666 --> 00:23:46,706
Let's take them out first.

424
00:23:47,208 --> 00:23:48,608
My hands were getting itchy anyway.

425
00:23:49,166 --> 00:23:50,166
You're asking for it.

426
00:23:59,750 --> 00:24:00,750
Run!

427
00:24:01,666 --> 00:24:02,208
Split up!

428
00:24:02,208 --> 00:24:03,208
After them!

429
00:24:10,458 --> 00:24:10,875
This way.

430
00:24:11,125 --> 00:24:12,125
They went this way.

431
00:24:12,625 --> 00:24:13,625
Check over there.

432
00:24:16,750 --> 00:24:17,166
Over here.

433
00:24:17,666 --> 00:24:18,666
Hurry!

434
00:24:19,791 --> 00:24:20,791
Where'd they go?

435
00:24:25,416 --> 00:24:26,125
It's a dead end.

436
00:24:26,250 --> 00:24:26,875
Let's look over there.

437
00:24:27,250 --> 00:24:28,250
Okay, sure.

438
00:24:29,750 --> 00:24:30,750
What are you doing here?

439
00:24:31,375 --> 00:24:32,392
Helping Uncle Wang mend some nets.

440
00:24:32,416 --> 00:24:33,416
To earn some extra cash.

441
00:24:34,208 --> 00:24:35,208
They went east.

442
00:24:36,041 --> 00:24:37,041
But they'll be back.

443
00:24:37,708 --> 00:24:38,500
You should wait a bit.

444
00:24:38,708 --> 00:24:40,108
If you go out now, they'll see you.

445
00:24:41,833 --> 00:24:42,833
What's wrong?

446
00:24:43,375 --> 00:24:44,375
It's nothing.

447
00:24:44,708 --> 00:24:45,708
You know this place well.

448
00:24:47,875 --> 00:24:49,000
I grew up on this dock.

449
00:24:49,750 --> 00:24:50,750
This part of the dock...

450
00:24:50,875 --> 00:24:53,195
used to be where my grandma
and I played hide-and-seek.

451
00:25:00,791 --> 00:25:02,311
About what happened at school today...

452
00:25:03,083 --> 00:25:03,625
I'm sorry.

453
00:25:03,750 --> 00:25:04,950
It was a big misunderstanding.

454
00:25:05,875 --> 00:25:06,875
I shouldn't have...

455
00:25:06,958 --> 00:25:08,518
jumped in without knowing the facts.

456
00:25:08,583 --> 00:25:09,583
It's just that kid...

457
00:25:09,958 --> 00:25:12,000
he doesn't look like a delivery boy.

458
00:25:14,208 --> 00:25:15,528
My mom's busy at the noodle shop.

459
00:25:16,333 --> 00:25:17,813
She doesn't have time to run errands.

460
00:25:19,291 --> 00:25:20,531
Bian Ye helps out at our place.

461
00:25:21,416 --> 00:25:22,416
He needs the money.

462
00:25:22,625 --> 00:25:23,875
And we need cheap labor.

463
00:25:25,583 --> 00:25:27,863
So my mom always has him
deliver lunch to me and Xu Nuo.

464
00:25:30,333 --> 00:25:31,773
Bian Ye does have a bit of a temper.

465
00:25:32,458 --> 00:25:34,378
He's always grumbling
when he delivers the food.

466
00:25:34,958 --> 00:25:35,958
But he always shows up.

467
00:25:37,791 --> 00:25:38,833
Why did you...

468
00:25:39,666 --> 00:25:40,866
insist on fighting Bian Ye?

469
00:25:44,333 --> 00:25:45,416
He rubbed me the wrong way.

470
00:25:46,416 --> 00:25:48,976
But you never get involved in
other people's business at school.

471
00:25:51,833 --> 00:25:53,273
I thought he was giving you trouble.

472
00:25:53,916 --> 00:25:55,516
I can't stand seeing people get bullied.

473
00:25:57,541 --> 00:25:58,541
You've got a tear.

474
00:25:59,250 --> 00:26:00,250
I do?

475
00:26:01,333 --> 00:26:02,693
Must have snagged it on something.

476
00:26:06,333 --> 00:26:07,333
Lift it up.

477
00:26:41,208 --> 00:26:42,208
There.

478
00:26:42,291 --> 00:26:43,291
It should be clear now.

479
00:26:43,958 --> 00:26:44,958
We should go.

480
00:26:53,958 --> 00:26:54,458
Stay close to me.

481
00:26:54,916 --> 00:26:55,916
Don't make a sound.

482
00:27:10,333 --> 00:27:11,333
This path...

483
00:27:11,833 --> 00:27:13,153
you know it surprisingly well.

484
00:27:13,541 --> 00:27:15,301
I didn't have any
friends when I was little.

485
00:27:15,791 --> 00:27:17,711
So I walked every one
of these alleys by myself.

486
00:27:20,458 --> 00:27:21,818
That way leads to the back street.

487
00:27:22,333 --> 00:27:23,613
Your villa is in that direction.

488
00:27:25,416 --> 00:27:25,875
What about you?

489
00:27:26,250 --> 00:27:27,250
Me?

490
00:27:27,458 --> 00:27:28,738
I'm going back to the warehouse.

491
00:27:28,875 --> 00:27:30,635
I haven't finished
mending the fishing nets.

492
00:27:31,541 --> 00:27:32,861
Are you that desperate for money?

493
00:27:34,083 --> 00:27:35,363
I still haven't saved up enough.

494
00:27:36,791 --> 00:27:37,791
Tomorrow...

495
00:27:38,458 --> 00:27:39,738
are we still on for tutoring?

496
00:27:40,250 --> 00:27:41,250
We are.

497
00:27:41,375 --> 00:27:42,375
Okay.

498
00:27:43,791 --> 00:27:44,791
Xu Yuan.

499
00:27:47,750 --> 00:27:48,750
Today...

500
00:27:50,750 --> 00:27:51,750
thank you.

501
00:27:52,875 --> 00:27:53,875
You helped me first.

502
00:27:54,500 --> 00:27:55,660
Even though it was a mistake.

503
00:28:07,166 --> 00:28:07,666
Bian Ye.

504
00:28:07,958 --> 00:28:09,059
If I don't break one of your legs today...

505
00:28:09,083 --> 00:28:10,203
I'll take your last name.

506
00:28:13,791 --> 00:28:14,583
Bian the dog.

507
00:28:14,791 --> 00:28:16,333
That's not much of a last name anyway.

508
00:28:16,416 --> 00:28:16,875
Who are you calling a dog?

509
00:28:16,916 --> 00:28:17,916
Stop!

510
00:28:48,375 --> 00:28:49,375
How much does he owe?

511
00:28:49,500 --> 00:28:50,500
What?

512
00:28:50,541 --> 00:28:51,541
I said...

513
00:28:51,750 --> 00:28:53,125
how much money does he owe you?

514
00:29:00,166 --> 00:29:01,166
His debt...

515
00:29:01,416 --> 00:29:02,416
I'll clear it.

516
00:29:03,333 --> 00:29:04,333
Can we go now?

517
00:29:05,916 --> 00:29:07,708
Found yourself a sugar mama already?

518
00:29:08,291 --> 00:29:09,291
Not bad.

519
00:29:10,166 --> 00:29:11,166
Let's go.

520
00:29:12,416 --> 00:29:13,416
Yeah, your mom.

521
00:29:14,416 --> 00:29:15,000
Let go of me.

522
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:16,000
Calm down.

523
00:29:16,750 --> 00:29:17,750
Don't forget...

524
00:29:17,833 --> 00:29:19,000
I'm your creditor now.

525
00:29:19,333 --> 00:29:20,333
Let go of me.

526
00:29:22,416 --> 00:29:23,416
Are you calm now?

527
00:29:23,666 --> 00:29:24,666
I'm not selling my body.

528
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:29,000
Don't worry.

529
00:29:29,416 --> 00:29:32,166
I'm not into kids.

530
00:29:32,541 --> 00:29:33,541
Then what do you want?

531
00:29:33,791 --> 00:29:35,751
Do doctors run a loan
shark business on the side?

532
00:29:35,833 --> 00:29:36,833
Starting tomorrow...

533
00:29:37,791 --> 00:29:40,551
you'll come to my place for two
hours of tutoring every afternoon.

534
00:29:40,666 --> 00:29:41,333
To pay off your debt.

535
00:29:41,541 --> 00:29:42,541
Tutoring?

536
00:29:43,583 --> 00:29:45,183
Do I look like the studying type to you?

537
00:29:45,291 --> 00:29:46,651
Whether you look like it or not...

538
00:29:47,166 --> 00:29:48,366
we'll find out when we try.

539
00:29:48,625 --> 00:29:49,625
Can you walk?

540
00:30:18,041 --> 00:30:19,041
My hand...

541
00:30:21,541 --> 00:30:22,541
it hurts a little.

542
00:30:22,583 --> 00:30:23,583
Tough it out.

543
00:30:27,541 --> 00:30:28,708
So now you feel the pain.

544
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:30,892
You weren't so scared when
you were fighting, were you?

545
00:30:30,916 --> 00:30:31,916
Who said I was scared?

546
00:30:32,500 --> 00:30:33,820
It's fine. It's just a small cut.

547
00:30:34,166 --> 00:30:35,559
If you don't treat a
small wound properly...

548
00:30:35,583 --> 00:30:36,903
it can get seriously infected.

549
00:30:44,166 --> 00:30:44,666
What's wrong?

550
00:30:44,833 --> 00:30:46,313
I think I pulled a muscle in my back.

551
00:30:46,666 --> 00:30:47,986
Let me give you some acupuncture.

552
00:30:48,625 --> 00:30:49,625
No, thanks.

553
00:30:50,375 --> 00:30:51,375
Trust me.

554
00:30:52,041 --> 00:30:53,041
I'm a doctor.

555
00:31:09,541 --> 00:31:10,541
How does it feel now?

556
00:31:12,791 --> 00:31:13,333
It's okay.

557
00:31:13,666 --> 00:31:14,666
Tomorrow at 5 p.m.

558
00:31:15,250 --> 00:31:16,250
Come to my place.

559
00:31:16,833 --> 00:31:17,500
I'll tutor you.

560
00:31:17,625 --> 00:31:18,625
I said I don't want to.

561
00:31:20,041 --> 00:31:21,208
You don't have a choice.

562
00:31:21,833 --> 00:31:22,833
Don't forget...

563
00:31:22,875 --> 00:31:23,916
I'm your creditor.

564
00:31:24,083 --> 00:31:25,523
I'll earn the money to pay you back.

565
00:31:27,500 --> 00:31:28,500
Perhaps...

566
00:31:28,791 --> 00:31:30,583
you'd prefer I go to your school gate...

567
00:31:31,291 --> 00:31:32,491
to pick you up after class?

568
00:31:33,875 --> 00:31:34,875
You're insane.

569
00:31:35,250 --> 00:31:36,930
You'll have to pull down your pants a bit.

570
00:31:37,208 --> 00:31:38,808
I need to needle your Huantiao acupoint.

571
00:31:40,500 --> 00:31:41,500
Trust me.

572
00:31:41,958 --> 00:31:42,958
I'm a doctor.

573
00:32:07,833 --> 00:32:08,500
Bian Ye is fine.

574
00:32:08,750 --> 00:32:09,750
I paid off his debt.

575
00:32:10,416 --> 00:32:11,416
Take care of yourself.

576
00:32:11,791 --> 00:32:13,791
Let me know if you feel anything unusual.

577
00:32:14,958 --> 00:32:16,598
Since you're here, you should study hard.

578
00:32:17,708 --> 00:32:19,416
That kid today seemed like a decent guy.

579
00:32:19,958 --> 00:32:20,958
Worth being friends with.

580
00:32:26,750 --> 00:32:27,750
Stay away from me.

581
00:32:28,166 --> 00:32:29,166
It's better for everyone.

582
00:32:29,708 --> 00:32:30,708
Watch out.

583
00:32:32,791 --> 00:32:33,791
This path...

584
00:32:34,250 --> 00:32:34,833
you know it surprisingly well.

585
00:32:35,041 --> 00:32:36,801
I didn't have any
friends when I was little.

586
00:32:37,166 --> 00:32:38,559
So I walked every one
of these alleys by myself.

587
00:32:38,583 --> 00:32:39,583
Today...

588
00:32:41,291 --> 00:32:41,916
thank you.

589
00:32:42,250 --> 00:32:43,250
You helped me first.

590
00:32:43,791 --> 00:32:44,951
Even though it was a mistake.

591
00:33:05,416 --> 00:33:06,416
Xu Yuan.

592
00:33:08,166 --> 00:33:09,750
What kind of person are you, really?

593
00:33:18,083 --> 00:33:19,083
Mom.

594
00:33:19,458 --> 00:33:20,666
Why are you so late?

595
00:33:21,125 --> 00:33:22,565
A classmate needed me for something.

596
00:33:22,875 --> 00:33:24,291
Look at the state you're in.

597
00:33:25,833 --> 00:33:26,833
Mom.

598
00:33:27,541 --> 00:33:28,541
Um...

599
00:33:28,875 --> 00:33:30,715
Is the paper box Granny
Chang left still here?

600
00:33:31,375 --> 00:33:31,958
Yes, it is.

601
00:33:32,208 --> 00:33:33,888
It's under your bed. I haven't touched it.

602
00:33:34,208 --> 00:33:34,750
Why?

603
00:33:34,750 --> 00:33:35,750
It's nothing.

604
00:33:35,916 --> 00:33:37,116
Mom, you should get some rest.
